1715 class StructuredFunctionWrapper(object):
1716   """A wrapper for `Defun` that supports structured arguments and return values.
1717   """
1718 
1719   def __init__(self, func, transformation_name, dataset=None,
1720                input_classes=None, input_shapes=None, input_types=None,
1721                add_to_graph=True, experimental_nested_dataset_support=False):
1722     """Creates a new `StructuredFunctionWrapper` for the given function.
1723 
1724     Args:
1725       func: A function from a nested structure to another nested structure.
1726       transformation_name: Human-readable name of the transformation in which
1727         this function is being instantiated, for error messages.
1728       dataset: (Optional.) A `tf.data.Dataset`. If given, the structure of this
1729         dataset will be assumed as the structure for `func` arguments; otherwise
1730         `input_classes`, `input_shapes`, and `input_types` must be defined.
1731       input_classes: (Optional.) A nested structure of `type`. If given, this
1732         argument defines the Python types for `func` arguments.
1733       input_shapes: (Optional.) A nested structure of `tf.TensorShape`. If
1734         given, this argument defines the shapes and structure for `func`
1735         arguments.
1736       input_types: (Optional.) A nested structure of `tf.DType`. If given, this
1737         argument defines the element types and structure for `func` arguments.
1738       add_to_graph: (Optional.) If `True`, the function will be added to the
1739         default graph.
1740       experimental_nested_dataset_support: (Optional.) If `True`, the function
1741         will support `tf.data.Dataset` objects as arguments and return values.
1742 
1743     Raises:
1744       ValueError: If an invalid combination of `dataset`, `input_classes`,
1745         `input_shapes`, and `input_types` is passed.
1746     """
1747     if dataset is None:
1748       if input_classes is None or input_shapes is None or input_types is None:
1749         raise ValueError("Either `dataset`, or all of `input_classes`, "
1750                          "`input_shapes`, and `input_types` must be specified.")
1751       self._input_shapes = input_shapes
1752       self._input_types = input_types
1753       self._input_classes = input_classes
1754     else:
1755       if not (input_classes is None and input_shapes is None and
1756               input_types is None):
1757         raise ValueError("Either `dataset`, or all of `input_classes`, "
1758                          "`input_shapes`, and `input_types` must be specified.")
1759       self._input_shapes = dataset.output_shapes
1760       self._input_types = dataset.output_types
1761       self._input_classes = dataset.output_classes
1762 
1763     self._transformation_name = transformation_name
1764 
1765     # TODO(b/110122868): Enable this support for all `tf.data` functions.
1766     self._nested_dataset_support = experimental_nested_dataset_support
1767 
1768     @function.Defun(*self._defun_args())
1769     def tf_data_structured_function_wrapper(*args):
1770       """Wrapper for passing nested structures to and from tf.data functions."""
1771       flat_args = []
1772       for arg, arg_class, arg_shape, arg_type in zip(
1773           args,
1774           nest.flatten(self._input_classes),
1775           nest.flatten(self._input_shapes),
1776           nest.flatten(self._input_types)):
1777         # TODO(b/110122868): Add a registration mechanism for new component
1778         # types.
1779         if arg_class is sparse_tensor_lib.SparseTensor:
1780           arg = sparse.deserialize_sparse_tensors(
1781               arg, arg_type, arg_shape, arg_class)
1782           arg.indices.set_shape([None, arg_shape.ndims])
1783           arg.dense_shape.set_shape([arg_shape.ndims])
1784         elif isinstance(arg_class, _NestedDatasetComponent):
1785           assert self._nested_dataset_support
1786           arg = _VariantDataset(arg, arg_class)
1787         else:
1788           arg.set_shape(arg_shape)
1789         flat_args.append(arg)
1790       nested_args = nest.pack_sequence_as(self._input_classes, flat_args)
1791       if not _should_unpack_args(nested_args):
1792         nested_args = (nested_args,)
1793 
1794       ret = func(*nested_args)
1795       # If `func` returns a list of tensors, `nest.flatten()` and
1796       # `ops.convert_to_tensor()` would conspire to attempt to stack
1797       # those tensors into a single tensor, because the customized
1798       # version of `nest.flatten()` does not recurse into lists. Since
1799       # it is more likely that the list arose from returning the
1800       # result of an operation (such as `tf.py_func()`) that returns a
1801       # list of not-necessarily-stackable tensors, we treat the
1802       # returned value is a `tuple` instead. A user wishing to pack
1803       # the return value into a single tensor can use an explicit
1804       # `tf.stack()` before returning.
1805       if isinstance(ret, list):
1806         ret = tuple(ret)
1807 
1808       # Convert any `SparseTensorValue`s to `SparseTensor`s and all other
1809       # values to tensors.
1810       flat_ret = []
1811       flat_classes = []
1812       flat_shapes = []
1813       flat_types = []
1814       for t in nest.flatten(ret):
1815         # TODO(b/110122868): Add a registration mechanism for new component
1816         # types.
1817         if sparse_tensor_lib.is_sparse(t):
1818           t = sparse_tensor_lib.SparseTensor.from_value(t)
1819           flat_ret.append(sparse.serialize_sparse_tensors(t))
1820           flat_classes.append(sparse_tensor_lib.SparseTensor)
1821           flat_shapes.append(t.get_shape())
1822           flat_types.append(t.dtype)
1823         elif isinstance(t, Dataset):
1824           if not self._nested_dataset_support:
1825             raise NotImplementedError(
1826                 "The %s transformation does not currently support nested "
1827                 "datasets as outputs." % self._transformation_name)
1828 
1829           flat_ret.append(t._as_variant_tensor())  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1830           component = _NestedDatasetComponent(t)
1831           flat_classes.append(component)
1832           flat_shapes.append(component)
1833           flat_types.append(component)
1834           if t.options() != Options():
1835             warnings.warn("Encountered a nested dataset with non-default "
1836                           "options. These options will not be propagated to "
1837                           "the outer dataset.")
1838         else:
1839           try:
1840             t = ops.convert_to_tensor(t)
1841           except (ValueError, TypeError):
1842             raise TypeError("Unsupported return value from function passed to "
1843                             "%s: %s." % (transformation_name, t))
1844           flat_ret.append(t)
1845           flat_classes.append(ops.Tensor)
1846           flat_shapes.append(t.get_shape())
1847           flat_types.append(t.dtype)
1848 
1849       ret = nest.pack_sequence_as(ret, flat_ret)
1850       self._output_classes = nest.pack_sequence_as(ret, flat_classes)
1851       self._output_shapes = nest.pack_sequence_as(ret, flat_shapes)
1852       self._output_types = nest.pack_sequence_as(ret, flat_types)
1853 
1854       _warn_if_collections(transformation_name)
1855 
1856       return flat_ret
1857 
1858     self._function = tf_data_structured_function_wrapper
1859     if add_to_graph:
1860       self._function.add_to_graph(ops.get_default_graph())
1861     else:
1862       # Use the private method that will execute
1863       # `tf_data_structured_function_wrapper` but delay adding it to the graph
1864       # in case (e.g.) we need to rerun the function.
1865       self._function._create_definition_if_needed()  # pylint: disable=protected-access
1866 
1867   def _defun_args(self):
1868     """Returns a flat list of `tf.DType` for the input element structure."""
1869     ret = []
1870     for input_type, input_class in zip(nest.flatten(self._input_types),
1871                                        nest.flatten(self._input_classes)):
1872       # TODO(b/110122868): Add a registration mechanism for new component types.
1873       if input_class is sparse_tensor_lib.SparseTensor:
1874         ret.append(dtypes.variant)
1875       elif isinstance(input_class, _NestedDatasetComponent):
1876         if not self._nested_dataset_support:
1877           raise NotImplementedError(
1878               "The %s transformation does not currently support nested "
1879               "datasets as inputs." % self._transformation_name)
1880         ret.append(dtypes.variant)
1881       else:
1882         assert isinstance(input_type, dtypes.DType)
1883         ret.append(input_type)
1884     return ret
1885 
1886   @property
1887   def output_classes(self):
1888     return self._output_classes
1889 
1890   @property
1891   def output_shapes(self):
1892     return self._output_shapes
1893 
1894   @property
1895   def output_types(self):
1896     return self._output_types
1897 
1898   @property
1899   def function(self):
1900     return self._function
1901 
1902 
1903 def flat_structure(dataset):
1904   """Helper for setting `output_shapes` and `output_types` attrs of Dataset ops.
1905 
1906   Most Dataset op constructors expect `output_shapes` and `output_types`
1907   arguments that represent the flattened structure of an element. This helper
1908   function generates these attrs as a keyword argument dictionary, allowing
1909   `Dataset._as_variant_tensor()` implementations to pass
1910   `**flat_structure(self)` to the op constructor.
1911 
1912   Args:
1913     dataset: A `tf.data.Dataset`.
1914 
1915   Returns:
1916     A dictionary of keyword arguments that can be passed to many Dataset op
1917     constructors.
1918   """
1919   output_classes = []
1920   output_shapes = []
1921   output_types = []
1922   for output_class, output_shape, output_type in zip(
1923       nest.flatten(dataset.output_classes), nest.flatten(dataset.output_shapes),
1924       nest.flatten(dataset.output_types)):
1925     if isinstance(output_class, _NestedDatasetComponent):
1926       output_classes.append(output_class.output_classes)
1927       output_shapes.append(output_shape.output_shapes)
1928       output_types.append(output_type.output_types)
1929     else:
1930       output_classes.append(output_class)
1931       output_shapes.append(output_shape)
1932       output_types.append(output_type)
1933 
1934   output_classes = nest.pack_sequence_as(dataset.output_classes, output_classes)
1935   output_shapes = nest.pack_sequence_as(dataset.output_shapes, output_shapes)
1936   output_types = nest.pack_sequence_as(dataset.output_types, output_types)
1937 
1938   return {
1939       "output_shapes":
1940           nest.flatten(sparse.as_dense_shapes(output_shapes, output_classes)),
1941       "output_types":
1942           nest.flatten(sparse.as_dense_types(output_types, output_classes)),
1943   }
1944 
1945 
1946 class _GeneratorDataset(DatasetSource):
1947   """A `Dataset` that generates elements by invoking a function."""
1948 
1949   def __init__(self, init_args, init_func, next_func, finalize_func):
1950     """Constructs a `_GeneratorDataset`.
1951 
1952     Args:
1953       init_args: A nested structure representing the arguments to `init_func`.
1954       init_func: A TensorFlow function that will be called on `init_args` each
1955         time a C++ iterator over this dataset is constructed. Returns a nested
1956         structure representing the "state" of the dataset.
1957       next_func: A TensorFlow function that will be called on the result of
1958         `init_func` to produce each element, and that raises `OutOfRangeError`
1959         to terminate iteration.
1960       finalize_func: A TensorFlow function that will be called on the result of
1961         `init_func` immediately before a C++ iterator over this dataset is
1962         destroyed. The return value is ignored.
1963     """
1964     super(_GeneratorDataset, self).__init__()
1965     # These members will be initialized by `tf_init_func`.
1966     self._state_classes = None
1967     self._state_shapes = None
1968     self._state_types = None
1969 
1970     self._init_args = init_args
1971 
1972     init_args_classes = sparse.get_classes(init_args)
1973     init_args_shapes = nest.pack_sequence_as(
1974         init_args, [t.get_shape() for t in nest.flatten(init_args)])
1975     init_args_types = nest.pack_sequence_as(
1976         init_args, [t.dtype for t in nest.flatten(init_args)])
1977 
1978     wrapped_init_func = StructuredFunctionWrapper(
1979         init_func, "GeneratorDataset", input_classes=init_args_classes,
1980         input_shapes=init_args_shapes, input_types=init_args_types)
1981     self._state_classes = wrapped_init_func.output_classes
1982     self._state_shapes = wrapped_init_func.output_shapes
1983     self._state_types = wrapped_init_func.output_types
1984     self._init_func = wrapped_init_func.function
1985 
1986     wrapped_next_func = StructuredFunctionWrapper(
1987         next_func, "GeneratorDataset", input_classes=self._state_classes,
1988         input_shapes=self._state_shapes, input_types=self._state_types)
1989     self._output_classes = wrapped_next_func.output_classes
1990     self._output_shapes = wrapped_next_func.output_shapes
1991     self._output_types = wrapped_next_func.output_types
1992     self._next_func = wrapped_next_func.function
1993 
1994     wrapped_finalize_func = StructuredFunctionWrapper(
1995         finalize_func, "GeneratorDataset", input_classes=self._state_classes,
1996         input_shapes=self._state_shapes, input_types=self._state_types)
1997     self._finalize_func = wrapped_finalize_func.function
1998 
1999   def _as_variant_tensor(self):
2000     return gen_dataset_ops.generator_dataset(
2001         nest.flatten(self._init_args) + self._init_func.captured_inputs,
2002         self._next_func.captured_inputs,
2003         self._finalize_func.captured_inputs,
2004         init_func=self._init_func,
2005         next_func=self._next_func,
2006         finalize_func=self._finalize_func,
2007         **flat_structure(self))
2008 
2009   @property
2010   def output_classes(self):
2011     return self._output_classes
2012 
2013   @property
2014   def output_shapes(self):
2015     return self._output_shapes
2016 
2017   @property
2018   def output_types(self):
2019     return self._output_types

2022 class ZipDataset(Dataset):
2023   """A `Dataset` that zips its inputs together."""

2025   def __init__(self, datasets):
2026     """See `Dataset.zip()` for details."""
2027     super(ZipDataset, self).__init__()
2028     for ds in nest.flatten(datasets):
2029       if not isinstance(ds, Dataset):
2030         if isinstance(ds, list):
2031           message = ("The argument to `Dataset.zip()` must be a nested "
2032                      "structure of `Dataset` objects. Nested structures do not "
2033                      "support Python lists; please use a tuple instead.")
2034         else:
2035           message = ("The argument to `Dataset.zip()` must be a nested "
2036                      "structure of `Dataset` objects.")
2037         raise TypeError(message)
2038     self._datasets = datasets
2039 
2040   def _as_variant_tensor(self):
2041     # pylint: disable=protected-access
2042     return gen_dataset_ops.zip_dataset(
2043         [ds._as_variant_tensor() for ds in nest.flatten(self._datasets)],
2044         **flat_structure(self))
2045     # pylint: enable=protected-access

2054         [ds.output_classes for ds in nest.flatten(self._datasets)])

2058     return nest.pack_sequence_as(
2059         self._datasets,

2061 
2062   @property
2063   def output_types(self):
2064     return nest.pack_sequence_as(
2065         self._datasets,
2066         [ds.output_types for ds in nest.flatten(self._datasets)])

2148 class RangeDataset(DatasetSource):
2149   """A `Dataset` of a step separated range of values."""
2150 
2151   def __init__(self, *args):
2152     """See `Dataset.range()` for details."""
2153     super(RangeDataset, self).__init__()
2154     self._parse_args(*args)
2155 
2156   def _parse_args(self, *args):
2157     """Parse arguments according to the same rules as the `range()` builtin."""
2158     if len(args) == 1:
2159       self._start = self._build_tensor(0, "start")
2160       self._stop = self._build_tensor(args[0], "stop")
2161       self._step = self._build_tensor(1, "step")
2162     elif len(args) == 2:
2163       self._start = self._build_tensor(args[0], "start")
2164       self._stop = self._build_tensor(args[1], "stop")
2165       self._step = self._build_tensor(1, "step")
2166     elif len(args) == 3:
2167       self._start = self._build_tensor(args[0], "start")
2168       self._stop = self._build_tensor(args[1], "stop")
2169       self._step = self._build_tensor(args[2], "step")
2170     else:
2171       raise ValueError("Invalid arguments to RangeDataset: %s" % str(args))
2172 
2173   def _build_tensor(self, int64_value, name):
2174     return ops.convert_to_tensor(int64_value, dtype=dtypes.int64, name=name)
2175 
2176   def _as_variant_tensor(self):
2177     return gen_dataset_ops.range_dataset(
2178         start=self._start,
2179         stop=self._stop,
2180         step=self._step,
2181         **flat_structure(self))
2182 
2183   @property
2184   def output_classes(self):
2185     return ops.Tensor
2186 
2187   @property
2188   def output_shapes(self):
2189     return tensor_shape.scalar()
2190 
2191   @property
2192   def output_types(self):
2193     return dtypes.int64

2225 class ShuffleDataset(UnaryDataset):
2226   """A `Dataset` that randomly shuffles the elements of its input."""
2227 
2228   def __init__(self,
2229                input_dataset,
2230                buffer_size,
2231                seed=None,
2232                reshuffle_each_iteration=None):
2233     """Randomly shuffles the elements of this dataset.
2234 
2235     Args:
2236       input_dataset: The input dataset.
2237       buffer_size: A `tf.int64` scalar `tf.Tensor`, representing the
2238         number of elements from this dataset from which the new
2239         dataset will sample.
2240       seed: (Optional.) A `tf.int64` scalar `tf.Tensor`, representing the
2241         random seed that will be used to create the distribution. See
2242         `tf.set_random_seed` for behavior.
2243       reshuffle_each_iteration: (Optional.) A boolean, which if true indicates
2244         that the dataset should be pseudorandomly reshuffled each time it is
2245         iterated over. (Defaults to `True`.)
2246 
2247     Returns:
2248       A `Dataset`.
2249 
2250     Raises:
2251       ValueError: if invalid arguments are provided.
2252     """
2253     super(ShuffleDataset, self).__init__(input_dataset)
2254     self._input_dataset = input_dataset
2255     self._buffer_size = ops.convert_to_tensor(
2256         buffer_size, dtype=dtypes.int64, name="buffer_size")
2257     self._seed, self._seed2 = random_seed.get_seed(seed)
2258     if reshuffle_each_iteration is None:
2259       self._reshuffle_each_iteration = True
2260     else:
2261       self._reshuffle_each_iteration = reshuffle_each_iteration
2262 
2263   def _as_variant_tensor(self):
2264     return gen_dataset_ops.shuffle_dataset(
2265         self._input_dataset._as_variant_tensor(),  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2266         buffer_size=self._buffer_size,
2267         seed=self._seed,
2268         seed2=self._seed2,
2269         reshuffle_each_iteration=self._reshuffle_each_iteration,
2270         **flat_structure(self))
2271 
2272   @property
2273   def output_classes(self):
2274     return self._input_dataset.output_classes
2275 
2276   @property
2277   def output_shapes(self):
2278     return self._input_dataset.output_shapes
2279 
2280   @property
2281   def output_types(self):
2282     return self._input_dataset.output_types

2385 
2386 def _is_padded_shape_compatible_with(padded_shape, input_component_shape):
2387   """Returns `True` if `input_component_shape` can be padded to `padded_shape`.
2388 
2389   Args:
2390     padded_shape: A `tf.TensorShape`.
2391     input_component_shape: A `tf.TensorShape`.
2392 
2393   Returns:
2394     `True` if `input_component_shape` can be padded to `padded_shape`, otherwise
2395     `False`.
2396   """
2397 
2398   if padded_shape.dims is None or input_component_shape.dims is None:
2399     return True
2400   if len(padded_shape.dims) != len(input_component_shape.dims):
2401     return False
2402   for padded_dim, input_dim in zip(
2403       padded_shape.dims, input_component_shape.dims):
2404     if (padded_dim.value is not None and input_dim.value is not None
2405         and padded_dim.value < input_dim.value):
2406       return False
2407   return True
2408 
2409 
2410 def _padded_shape_to_tensor(padded_shape, input_component_shape):
2411   """Converts `padded_shape` to a `tf.Tensor` representing that shape.
2412 
2413   Args:
2414     padded_shape: A shape-like object, which may be a `tf.TensorShape`, a Python
2415       sequence, or a 1-D `tf.Tensor` of `tf.int64` elements.
2416     input_component_shape: A `tf.TensorShape`, with which `padded_shape` must
2417       be compatible.
2418 
2419   Returns:
2420     A 1-D `tf.Tensor` of `tf.int64` elements, representing `padded_shape`.
2421 
2422   Raises:
2423     ValueError: If `padded_shape` is not a shape or not compatible with
2424       `input_component_shape`.
2425     TypeError: If `padded_shape` is not convertible to a `tf.int64` tensor.
2426   """
2427   try:
2428     # Try to convert the `padded_shape` to a `tf.TensorShape`
2429     padded_shape_as_shape = tensor_shape.as_shape(padded_shape)
2430     # We will return the "canonical" tensor representation, which uses
2431     # `-1` in place of `None`.
2432     ret = ops.convert_to_tensor(
2433         [dim if dim is not None else -1
2434          for dim in padded_shape_as_shape.as_list()], dtype=dtypes.int64)
2435   except (TypeError, ValueError):
2436     # The argument was not trivially convertible to a
2437     # `tf.TensorShape`, so fall back on the conversion to tensor
2438     # machinery.
2439     ret = ops.convert_to_tensor(padded_shape, preferred_dtype=dtypes.int64)
2440     if ret.shape.dims is not None and len(ret.shape.dims) != 1:
2441       raise ValueError(
2442           "Padded shape %s must be a 1-D tensor of tf.int64 values, but its "
2443           "shape was %s." % (padded_shape, ret.shape))
2444     if ret.dtype != dtypes.int64:
2445       raise TypeError(
2446           "Padded shape %s must be a 1-D tensor of tf.int64 values, but its "
2447           "element type was %s." % (padded_shape, ret.dtype.name))
2448     padded_shape_as_shape = tensor_util.constant_value_as_shape(ret)
2449 
2450   if not _is_padded_shape_compatible_with(padded_shape_as_shape,
2451                                           input_component_shape):
2452     raise ValueError("The padded shape %s is not compatible with the "
2453                      "corresponding input component shape %s."
2454                      % (padded_shape_as_shape, input_component_shape))
2455 
2456   return ret
2457 
2458 
2459 def _padding_value_to_tensor(value, output_type):
2460   """Converts the padding value to a tensor.
2461 
2462   Args:
2463     value: The padding value.
2464     output_type: Its expected dtype.
2465 
2466   Returns:
2467     A scalar `Tensor`.
2468 
2469   Raises:
2470     ValueError: if the padding value is not a scalar.
2471     TypeError: if the padding value's type does not match `output_type`.
2472   """
2473   value = ops.convert_to_tensor(value, name="padding_value")
2474   if not value.shape.is_compatible_with(tensor_shape.scalar()):
2475     raise ValueError("Padding value should be a scalar, but is not: %s" % value)
2476   if value.dtype != output_type:
2477     raise TypeError("Padding value tensor (%s) does not match output type: %s" %
2478                     (value, output_type))
2479   return value
2480 
2481 
2482 def _default_padding(input_dataset):
2483   """Returns default padding tensors in a structure matching `input_dataset`."""
2484   def make_zero(t):
2485     if t.base_dtype == dtypes.string:
2486       return ""
2487     elif t.base_dtype == dtypes.variant:
2488       raise TypeError("Unable to create padding for field of type 'variant'")
2489     else:
2490       return np.zeros_like(t.as_numpy_dtype())
2491 
2492   return nest.map_structure(make_zero, input_dataset.output_types)
2493 
2494 
2495 class PaddedBatchDataset(UnaryDataset):
2496   """A `Dataset` that batches and pads contiguous elements from its input."""
2497 
2498   def __init__(self, input_dataset, batch_size, padded_shapes, padding_values,
2499                drop_remainder):
2500     """See `Dataset.batch()` for details."""
2501     super(PaddedBatchDataset, self).__init__(input_dataset)
2502     if sparse.any_sparse(input_dataset.output_classes):
2503       # TODO(b/63669786): support batching of sparse tensors
2504       raise TypeError(
2505           "Batching of padded sparse tensors is not currently supported")
2506     self._input_dataset = input_dataset
2507     self._batch_size = ops.convert_to_tensor(
2508         batch_size, dtype=dtypes.int64, name="batch_size")
2509     padding_values = (
2510         padding_values
2511         if padding_values is not None else _default_padding(input_dataset))
2512 
2513     flat_padded_shapes = nest.flatten_up_to(input_dataset.output_shapes,
2514                                             padded_shapes)
2515 
2516     flat_padded_shapes_as_tensors = []
2517 
2518     for input_component_shape, padded_shape in zip(
2519         nest.flatten(input_dataset.output_shapes), flat_padded_shapes):
2520       flat_padded_shapes_as_tensors.append(
2521           _padded_shape_to_tensor(padded_shape, input_component_shape))
2522 
2523     self._padded_shapes = nest.pack_sequence_as(input_dataset.output_shapes,
2524                                                 flat_padded_shapes_as_tensors)
2525 
2526     self._padding_values = nest.map_structure_up_to(
2527         input_dataset.output_shapes, _padding_value_to_tensor, padding_values,
2528         input_dataset.output_types)
2529     self._drop_remainder = ops.convert_to_tensor(
2530         drop_remainder, dtype=dtypes.bool, name="drop_remainder")
2531 
2532   def _as_variant_tensor(self):
2533     # TODO(jsimsa): Switch to using v2 only any time after 6/30/2018.
2534     if smart_cond.smart_constant_value(self._drop_remainder) is False:
2535       return gen_dataset_ops.padded_batch_dataset(
2536           self._input_dataset._as_variant_tensor(),  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2537           batch_size=self._batch_size,
2538           padded_shapes=[
2539               ops.convert_to_tensor(s, dtype=dtypes.int64)
2540               for s in nest.flatten(self._padded_shapes)
2541           ],
2542           padding_values=nest.flatten(self._padding_values),
2543           output_shapes=nest.flatten(
2544               sparse.as_dense_shapes(self.output_shapes, self.output_classes)))
2545     else:
2546       return gen_dataset_ops.padded_batch_dataset_v2(
2547           self._input_dataset._as_variant_tensor(),  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2548           batch_size=self._batch_size,
2549           padded_shapes=[
2550               ops.convert_to_tensor(s, dtype=dtypes.int64)
2551               for s in nest.flatten(self._padded_shapes)
2552           ],
2553           padding_values=nest.flatten(self._padding_values),
2554           drop_remainder=self._drop_remainder,
2555           output_shapes=nest.flatten(
2556               sparse.as_dense_shapes(self.output_shapes, self.output_classes)))
2557 
2558   @property
2559   def output_classes(self):
2560     return self._input_dataset.output_classes
2561 
2562   @property
2563   def output_shapes(self):
2564 
2565     def _padded_shape_to_batch_shape(s):
2566       return tensor_shape.vector(
2567           tensor_util.constant_value(self._batch_size) if smart_cond.
2568           smart_constant_value(self._drop_remainder) else None).concatenate(
2569               tensor_util.constant_value_as_shape(s))
2570 
2571     return nest.map_structure(_padded_shape_to_batch_shape, self._padded_shapes)
2572 
2573   @property
2574   def output_types(self):
2575     return self._input_dataset.output_types
2576

2578 def _should_unpack_args(args):
2579   """Returns `True` if `args` should be `*args` when passed to a callable."""
2580   return type(args) is tuple  # pylint: disable=unidiomatic-typecheck

2583 def _warn_if_collections(transformation_name):
2584   """Prints warning message if the current graph uses common graph collections.
2585 
2586   NOTE(mrry): Currently a warning is only generated for lookup tables. Any
2587   variables created will be automatically hoisted out to the outermost scope
2588   using `init_scope()`. Some collections (such as for control-flow contexts)
2589   are benign and should not generate a warning.
2590 
2591   Args:
2592     transformation_name: A human-readable name for the transformation.
2593   """
2594   if ops.get_default_graph().get_collection(ops.GraphKeys.TABLE_INITIALIZERS):
2595     warnings.warn("Creating lookup tables inside a function passed to %s is not"
2596                   " supported. Create each table outside the function, and "
2597                   "capture it inside the function to use it."
2598                   % transformation_name)

2810   def _as_variant_tensor(self):

2812         self._input_dataset._as_variant_tensor(),  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2813         buffer_size=self._buffer_size,
2814         **flat_structure(self))
2815 
2816   @property
2817   def output_classes(self):
2818     return self._input_dataset.output_classes
2819 
2820   @property
2821   def output_shapes(self):
2822     return self._input_dataset.output_shapes
2823 
2824   @property
2825   def output_types(self):
2826     return self._input_dataset.output_types
2827

2829 class WindowDataset(UnaryDataset):
2830   """A dataset that creates window datasets from the input elements."""
2831 
2832   def __init__(self, input_dataset, size, shift, stride, drop_remainder):
2833     """See `window_dataset()` for more details."""
2834     super(WindowDataset, self).__init__(input_dataset)
2835     self._input_dataset = input_dataset
2836     self._size = ops.convert_to_tensor(size, dtype=dtypes.int64, name="size")
2837     self._shift = ops.convert_to_tensor(shift, dtype=dtypes.int64, name="shift")
2838     self._stride = ops.convert_to_tensor(
2839         stride, dtype=dtypes.int64, name="stride")
2840     self._drop_remainder = ops.convert_to_tensor(
2841         drop_remainder, dtype=dtypes.bool, name="drop_remainder")
2842     self._output_classes = nest.pack_sequence_as(
2843         input_dataset.output_classes,
2844         [
2845             _NestedDatasetComponent(  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2846                 output_classes=output_class,
2847                 output_shapes=output_shape,
2848                 output_types=output_type)
2849             for output_class, output_shape, output_type in zip(
2850                 nest.flatten(input_dataset.output_classes),
2851                 nest.flatten(input_dataset.output_shapes),
2852                 nest.flatten(input_dataset.output_types))
2853         ])
2854     self._output_shapes = self._output_classes
2855     self._output_types = self._output_classes
2856 
2857   def _as_variant_tensor(self):
2858     return gen_dataset_ops.window_dataset(
2859         self._input_dataset._as_variant_tensor(),  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2860         self._size,
2861         self._shift,
2862         self._stride,
2863         self._drop_remainder,
2864         **flat_structure(self))
2865 
2866   @property
2867   def output_classes(self):
2868     return self._output_classes
2869 
2870   @property
2871   def output_shapes(self):
2872     return self._output_shapes
2873 
2874   @property
2875   def output_types(self):
2876     return self._output_types
2877

2879 class _OptionsDataset(UnaryDataset):
2880   """An identity `Dataset` that stores options."""
2881 
2882   def __init__(self, input_dataset, options):
2883     super(_OptionsDataset, self).__init__(input_dataset)
2884     self._input_dataset = input_dataset
2885     self._options = input_dataset.options()
2886     if self._options:
2887       self._options = self._options.merge(options)
2888     else:
2889       self._options = options
2890 
2891   def _as_variant_tensor(self):
2892     return self._input_dataset._as_variant_tensor()  # pylint: disable=protected-access
2893 
2894   def options(self):
2895     return self._options
2896 
2897   @property
2898   def output_classes(self):
2899     return self._input_dataset.output_classes
2900

2902   def output_shapes(self):
2903     return self._input_dataset.output_shapes
2904 
2905   @property
2906   def output_types(self):
2907     return self._input_dataset.output_types
